00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:42,760
where Marcus Brutus despised Caesar,

388
00:22:43,480 --> 00:22:47,500
okay? All right,

389
00:22:47,540 --> 00:22:48,800
so it's a very complicated situation.

390
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:52,720
But what unites everyone is

391
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:55,760
that, is the feeling that

392
00:22:55,760 --> 00:22:57,600
Rome was changing too fast.

393
00:22:58,020 --> 00:22:59,900
Okay? So remember, Julius Caesar,

394
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:04,360
he did what he did in order to save
the Republic, to restore the Republic.

395
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:07,700
And so when he had obtained power,

396
00:23:08,300 --> 00:23:10,900
he was making changes that were necessary,

