00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,240
Okay? So

429
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:07,560
there are lots of taboos in Rome.

430
00:25:08,720 --> 00:25:11,680
One major taboo is the
idea of the promerium.

431
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:17,540
Okay? The promerium just
means the boundary of Rome.

432
00:25:17,700 --> 00:25:20,120
And the idea here is that Rome,

433
00:25:20,260 --> 00:25:23,800
the city of Rome, the physical
geographic space of Rome,

434
00:25:23,940 --> 00:25:25,560
it is sacred and divine.

435
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:28,360
It is protected by the gods.

436
00:25:28,780 --> 00:25:33,580
And therefore, you are not allowed
to bring weapons into Rome.

437
00:25:33,820 --> 00:25:36,700
Okay? If you're a soldier, you
must come in as a private citizen.

438
00:25:37,020 --> 00:25:39,020
You must come in as a soldier. You are
not allowed to come in as a soldier.

439
00:25:39,760 --> 00:25:42,020
You are not allowed to
commit acts of violence

440
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:43,900
within the promerium.

441
00:25:44,740 --> 00:25:47,020
Otherwise, the gods will spite you.

442
00:25:47,300 --> 00:25:49,260
The gods will take vengeance against you.

443
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:52,000
Okay? So that's the first taboo.

444
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:58,680
Second taboo is this. The Senate
is considered the most sacred

445
00:25:58,680 --> 00:26:00,340
and divine space in the entire,

446
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:03,200
in all of Rome.

447
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:07,140
And so no one's allowed to bring weapons.

448
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:10,600
No one's allowed to commit
violence in the Senate.

449
00:26:11,180 --> 00:26:12,860
Okay? Also,

450
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:16,320
the Senate's laws are
basically the laws of the gods.

451
00:26:16,780 --> 00:26:22,460
The Senate declared the body of
Julius Caesar to be sacrosanct.

452
00:26:22,540 --> 00:26:24,080
Okay? Meaning divine and sacred.

453
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:26,240
You are not allowed to touch
the body of Julius Caesar.

454
00:26:28,780 --> 00:26:31,740
Okay? The third thing is

455
00:26:31,740 --> 00:26:36,940
that everyone in the Senate was
personally appointed by Julius Caesar.

456
00:26:37,140 --> 00:26:42,500
So everyone owed their good fortune
to the generosity of Julius Caesar.

457
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:47,840
Okay? Do you understand? It was just
unimaginable for Julius Caesar to think

458
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:51,640
that his friends could be
conspiring against him.

459
00:26:52,860 --> 00:26:55,000
Okay? Okay.

460
00:26:55,040 --> 00:26:56,380
Does that make sense so far, guys?

461
00:26:57,280 --> 00:26:58,320
Okay, it was beyond the

462
00:26:58,320 --> 00:27:04,260
imagination of Julius Caesar.

463
00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:07,980
But if this is true, then
something else is true,

464
00:27:08,080 --> 00:27:11,420
which is that Julius Caesar
did not want to become king.

