00:27:25,020 --> 00:27:29,080
he, like all Romans,
believed in these taboos.

469
00:27:30,420 --> 00:27:34,380
And the ultimate taboo was Rome
could never, should never be king.

470
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:38,380
So he himself did not want to become king.

471
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:40,620
He was behaving very arrogantly.

472
00:27:40,820 --> 00:27:42,240
He was behaving like a king.

473
00:27:42,700 --> 00:27:45,900
But he did not, but he would
not become king himself.

474
00:27:46,100 --> 00:27:48,540
Because it would go
against the Roman Republic.

475
00:27:48,860 --> 00:27:53,600
It would defy all the taboos
of the Roman Republic.

476
00:27:54,220 --> 00:27:56,920
Okay? And also, before Caesar,

477
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:59,760
there was also another
dictator named Sulla.

478
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:03,280
Okay? And this example of
Sulla is, he's a man who

